      "title": "FCFS Scheduling",
      "difficulty": "Hard",
      "topic": "Process Management",
      "description": "Given processes with arrival times: P1(0, 5), P2(1, 3), P3(2, 8), P4(3, 6) where first number is arrival time and second is burst time. Calculate the average waiting time using FCFS scheduling.",
      "inputFormat": "No input required.",
      "outputFormat": "Print the average waiting time as a decimal number.",
      "constraints": "Single numeric answer expected.",
      "examples": [
        {
          "input": "",
          "output": "4.75"
        }
      ],
      "explanation": "FCFS executes in arrival order. P1: wait=0, P2: wait=5-1=4, P3: wait=8-2=6, P4: wait=16-3=13. Average = (0+4+6+13)/4 = 23/4 = 5.75. Correction: P1 completes at 5, P2 at 8, P3 at 16, P4 at 22. Wait times: P1=0, P2=8-1-3=4, P3=16-2-8=6, P4=22-3-6=13. Average = (0+4+6+13)/4 = 5.75",
